'''Dănuţ Marcu''' (born 11 January 1952) is a [[Romania]]n [[mathematician]] and [[computer scientist]], who received his [[Ph.D.]] from the [[University of Bucharest]] in 1981. He claimed to have authored more than 400 scientific papers.<ref>[http://www.oocities.org/drmarcu/PP_DM.html Marcu's personal web page].</ref>
Marcu was frequently accused of [[plagiarism]].<ref>{{citation|title=1.8 A notorious mathematical problem|work=Graduate Skills Courses: Good practice in citation and the avoidance of plagiarism|publisher=[[Oxford University]]|accessdate=2013-03-05|quote=it is his reputation as a prolific plagiariser of academic papers which is the source of his notoriety in the academic and publishing communities|url=http://tallcourses.conted.ox.ac.uk/plagiarism/xhtml/introduction/ANotoriousMathematicalProblem.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130419144029/http://tallcourses.conted.ox.ac.uk/plagiarism/xhtml/introduction/ANotoriousMathematicalProblem.html|archivedate=2013-04-19|df=}}.</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Plagiarism in Academia|first=Syed|last=Shahabuddin|url=http://www.isetl.org/ijtlhe/pdf/IJTLHE641.pdf|journal=International Journal of Teaching and Learning in Higher Education|volume=21|year=2009|issue=3|pages=353–359}}. This paper quotes {{harvtxt|Boussou|Martello|Plastria|2006}} concerning Marcu, including the quote from an unnamed "well-known mathematician" that "Marcu is a notorious plagiarist".</ref><ref>{{citation|title=On ethics, the pursuit of knowledge, truth and status in the hallowed halls of academe|first1=John S.|last1=Buckeridge|first2=Rob|last2=Watts|journal=Integrative Zoology|year=2012|doi=10.1111/j.1749-4877.2012.12007.x|quote=Individual cases of academic plagiarism continue to attract significant media attention. Mathematician and computer scientist Danut Marcu claimed to have published over 383 original papers in various scientific publications. A number of his recent papers were shown to be exact copies of papers published earlier by other authors.}}.</ref><ref>{{citation|title=The Fox in the Hen House: A Critical Examination of Plagiarism Among Members of the Academy of Management|first1=Benson|last1=Honig|first2=Akansha|last2=Bedi|journal=Academy of Management Learning & Education|year=2012|volume=11|url=http://responsable.unige.ch/Documents/Plagiarism.pdf|issue=1|pages=101–123|quote=Another example of a habitual plagiarizer is found in the field of management sciences, where author Dănuț Marcu published three plagiarized papers in ''Studia Universitatis Babes-Bolyai Series Informatica'' during 2002–2003 and subsequently tried to publish another “lifted” piece in the ''Quarterly Journal of Operations Research'' ... Marcu was subsequently “outed” and banned from publishing his work in the above journals. The plagiarized rejected piece from 4OR was later published in another journal.}}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The editors of ''Studia Universitatis Babeş-Bolyai, Informatica'' decided to ban Marcu from their journal for this reason,<ref>{{cite journal | author = The editors | url = http://www.cs.ubbcluj.ro/~studia-i/2004-1/0-FromEditors.pdf | title = Apology on plagiarism papers | journal = Studia Universitatis Babeş-Bolyai, Informatica | volume = 49 | year = 2004 | pages = 112}}</ref> as did the editors of ''4OR: A Quarterly Journal of Operations Research''<ref>{{cite journal | author = Denis Bouyssou, Silvano Martello, and [[Frank Plastria]] | url = http://l1.lamsade.dauphine.fr/~bouyssou/Marcu.pdf | title = The Case of plagiarism: Dănuţ Marcu (editorial note) | journal = 4OR: A Quarterly Journal of Operations Research | volume = 4 | year = 2006 | pages = 11–13 | issn = 1619-4500 | doi = 10.1007/s10288-006-0087-0}} See also [http://homepages.vub.ac.be/~fouror/DanutMarcuSoCalledPublications.pdf Graph Theory publications “authored” by Dănuţ Marcu] and [http://homepages.vub.ac.be/~fouror/plagiarism.pdf an example] (compare with [http://www.combinatorics.org/Volume_2/PDFFiles/v2i1n2.pdf the original]) at the 4OR website.</ref><ref>Editorial note by Bouyssou, Martello, and Plastria [http://homepages.vub.ac.be/~fouror/EditorialPlagiarism2009.pdf Plagiarism again: Sreenivas and Srinivas, with an update on Marcu] at the 4OR website</ref> and the editors of ''[[Geombinatorics]]''.<ref>{{cite journal | author = [[Alexander Soifer|Soifer, Alexander]] | title = The Case of Dr. Dănuţ Marcu: Serial Plagiarism and Signing False Statements | url = http://geombina.uccs.edu/?page_id=88 | journal = Geombinatorics | volume = XVI | issue = 3 | year = 2007 | pages = 293–296 }} One of the plagiarized works discovered by Soifer was written by noted mail-bomber [[Theodore Kaczynski]].</ref> The editors of ''[[Geometriae Dedicata]]'' state that they suspect Marcu of plagiarism, as he submitted a manuscript which is "more-or-less word for word the same" as a paper by Bernt Lindström.<ref>Karl Strambach and Ferdinand D. Veldkamp, "[http://www.springerlink.com/content/k7rm674498665241/ Editorial statement]", ''Geometriae Dedicata'' '''32''' (1989), p. 253; see also {{Zbl|0701.51004}} and {{MR|1038400}}.</ref> Jerrold W. Grossman, Sanpei Kageyama, Martin R. Pettet, and anonymous reviewers have accused Marcu of plagiarism in [[MathSciNet]] reviews.<ref>MathSciNet Reviews {{MR|2192785}}, {{MR|2097141}}, {{MR|2060125}}, {{MR|2031651}}, {{MR|2031645}}, {{MR|2024191}}, {{MR|1961850}}, and {{MR|1899818}} by Grossman; MathSciNet Review {{MR|1666961}} by Kageyama; MathSciNet Review {{MR|1795035}} by Pettet; MathSciNet Reviews {{MR|1856038}}, {{MR|1739530}}, {{MR|1427830}}, and {{MR|1324075}} by anonymous reviewers.</ref> According to the managing editors of ''Menemui Matematik'', Marcu's paper in that journal is a well known result in [[graph theory]], and the paper "should not have been published".<ref>{{MR|2281788}}</ref>
