{{defn|no=4|An asymmetry}}

{{term|action}}
{{defn|{{main|action (physics)}} A function ''S'' on the space of fields given (formally) by the integral of the Lagrangian density over spacetime, whose stationary points are the solutions of the equations of motion.}}

{{term|ADE}}
{{defn|{{main|ADE classification}} Refers to the ADE classification (A<sub>''n''</sub>,D<sub>n</sub>, E<sub>6</sub>, E<sub>7</sub>, E<sub>8</sub>)  of simply laced [[Dynkin diagram]]s, and to several related classifications of Lie algebras, singularities and so on. }}

