{{term|photon}}
{{defn|{{main|photon}} The neutral spin 1 gauge boson of the electromagnetic field.}}

{{term|PMNS}}
{{defn| [[Pontecorvo–Maki–Nakagawa–Sakata matrix]] for neutrino mixing}}

{{term|Polyakov action}}
{{defn|{{main|Polyakov action}} A modification of the Nambu–Goto action for strings that eliminates the square root.}}

{{term|PQ}}
{{defn|Peccei–Quinn, as in [[Peccei–Quinn theory]].}}

{{term|pQCD}}
{{term|PQCD}}
{{defn|Perturbative [[quantum chromodynamics]].}}

{{term|prepotential}}
{{defn|A function used to construct the vector superfield in [[supersymmetric gauge theory]] and [[Seiberg–Witten theory]].}}

{{term|primary field}}
{{defn|A field killed by the positive weight operators of the Virasoro algebra (or similar algebra); in other words, a lowest weight vector.}}

{{term|Princeton string quartet}}
{{defn|[[David Gross]], [[Jeffrey A. Harvey|Jeffrey Harvey]], [[Emil Martinec]], and [[Ryan Rohm]], who introduced the [[heterotic string]] in 1985.}}

{{term|PSL}}
{{defn|[[Projective special linear group]].}}

