{{defn|{{main|Supermultiplet}} A representation of a [[supersymmetry algebra]]}}

{{term|superpotential}}
{{defn|{{main|Superpotential}} A function of chiral superfield not depending on their superderivatives or spacetime derivatives, used to form a Lagrangian.}}

{{term|superspace}}
{{defn|{{main|superspace}} A supersymmetric analogue of spacetime}}

{{term|superstring}}
{{defn|{{main|superstring}} A supersymmetric analogue of a string}}

{{term|supersymmetry}}
{{defn|{{main|supersymmetry|supersymmetry algebra}} A generalization of a [[Lie superalgebra]], where the Lie bracket [''a'',''b''] is sometimes given by ''ab''+''ba'' rather than ''ab''–''ba''.}}

{{term|SUSY}}
{{defn|An abbreviation for [[supersymmetry]].}}

