{{Infobox galaxy | name = Markarian 335 | image = | caption = | epoch = [[J2000]] | constellation name = [[Pegasus (constellation)|Pegasus]] | ra = {{RA|00|06|19.582}}<ref name=2MASS>{{cite journal|title=The Two Micron All Sky Survey (2MASS)|author=Skrutskie, M.|display-authors=etal|journal=The Astronomical Journal|volume=131|issue=2|pages=1163–1183|year=2006|doi=10.1086/498708|bibcode=2006AJ....131.1163S}}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|+20|12|10.58}}<ref name=2MASS/> | z = 7730 km/s<ref name=NED>{{cite web|url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/cgi-bin/nph-objsearch?objname=Markarian+335&extend=no&out_csys=Equatorial&out_equinox=J2000.0&obj_sort=RA+or+Longitude&of=pre_text&zv_breaker=30000.0&list_limit=5&img_stamp=YES|title=NED results for object MRK 0335|publisher=[[National Aeronautics and Space Administration]] / [[Infrared Processing and Analysis Center]]|work=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref> | h_radial_v = 0.025785<ref name=NED/> | dist_ly = {{cvt|150.300|±|66.654|Mpc|Mly|order=flip|lk=on}}<ref name=NED/> | type = | mass = | size = | appmag_v = 13.85<ref name=SIMBAD>{{cite simbad|title=Mrk 335|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref> | appmag_b = 14.19<ref name=SIMBAD/> | absmag_v = | size_v = 0.187′<ref name=SIMBAD/> | names = {{odlist|name=INTREF 2|PGC=473|2MASS=J00061953+2012105}}<ref name=SIMBAD/> }} '''Markarian 335''' is a [[Seyfert galaxy]] containing a [[supermassive black hole]], located 324 million light-years away in the constellation of [[Pegasus (constellation)|Pegasus]].
The central black hole in this active galaxy nucleus is notable for its [[corona]]'s spinning rate (at about 20 percent the speed of light) and its change in brightness from 2007 to 2014. The geometry of the corona has been deduced from [[Theory of relativity|relativistic]] blurring of the reflection of the [[accretion disc]]. An [[x-ray]] flare in 2013 is interpreted as an aborted jet.<ref name=wilkins/>
